@startuml DockerSandboxExperiment
' EXPERIMENT — what Docker Sandboxes (sbx) would subsume in proveo's bespoke
' isolation stack, and what it would NOT. Exploratory; not a decision to adopt.
'
' Docker Sandboxes research (2026-07, sbx v0.35.0 — "generally stable", pre-GA):
'   https://docs.docker.com/ai/sandboxes/                     — landing (microVM per workspace)
'   https://docs.docker.com/ai/sandboxes/architecture/        — hypervisor boundary; own kernel + engine + net
'   https://docs.docker.com/ai/sandboxes/security/isolation/  — deny-by-default egress; cred injection
'   https://docs.docker.com/ai/sandboxes/security/defaults/   — locked-down defaults
'   https://docs.docker.com/ai/sandboxes/usage/               — sbx run/exec/cp/ports/policy/secret
'   https://docs.docker.com/ai/sandboxes/customize/kits/      — Kit spec.yaml (declarative config)
'   https://www.docker.com/blog/docker-sandboxes-run-agents-in-yolo-mode-safely/
'
' proveo bespoke stack this would collapse (source of the "TODAY" boxes):
'   internal/egress/{plan,exec,stage}.go  — networks/sidecars/teardown (firewall = 3 nets + Squid + MITM)
'   internal/egressproxy/*                 — TLS-MITM proxy + per-session CA + NDJSON flows
'   internal/broker/broker.go              — credential inject / strip
'   internal/egresspolicy/*                — DLP secret scanner (regex + base64/hex + entropy + sink denylist)
'   internal/dind/dind.go + defs/sidecars/dind    — privileged docker:dind sidecar
'   internal/runner/runner.go + defs/base/proveo-harden — cap-drop/no-new-priv/pids-limit + setuid strip
'   packages/lib/entrypoint-lib.sh         — arbitrary run-as-uid + HOME/passwd synth
'   internal/egress/exec.go + cmd/proveo/clean.go — teardown + leaked-artifact reaper
!includeurl https://raw.githubusercontent.com/proveo-ca/identity/refs/heads/main/proveo.iuml
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam componentStyle rectangle
skinparam nodesep 12
skinparam ranksep 60

title Experiment — proveo on Docker Sandboxes (""sbx"")\na per-workspace microVM subsumes most of the hand-built isolation stack (with real trade-offs)

package "TODAY — proveo bespoke isolation\n~2,800 LOC Go · 10 pkgs · 5 sidecars · 3 nets · per-session MITM CA" as today #FBECEC {
  component "egress planner\ninternal/egress\nnets · sidecars · DNS blackhole · teardown" as p_egress
  component "MITM proxy + per-session CA\ninternal/egressproxy" as p_mitm
  component "credential broker\ninternal/broker\ninject on-provider · strip off-provider" as p_broker
  component "DLP secret scanner\ninternal/egresspolicy\nregex · base64/hex · entropy · sink denylist" as p_dlp
  component "privileged DinD sidecar\ninternal/dind + docker:dind" as p_dind
  component "hardening\ninternal/runner + defs/base/proveo-harden\ncap-drop · no-new-priv · setuid strip" as p_harden
  component "run-as-uid + HOME/passwd synth\npackages/lib/entrypoint-lib.sh" as p_uid
  component "ephemeral lifecycle + leak reaper\nexec.go teardown + clean.go" as p_life
}

package "WITH sbx — Docker Sandboxes microVM\nhypervisor boundary · standalone sbx CLI · v0.35 (pre-GA)" as sbx #EBF3EC {
  component "sbx run «agent» «workspace»\none command; one microVM per workspace" as s_run
  component "Kit spec.yaml\nnetwork.allowedDomains / deniedDomains\ncredentials · environment  (deny wins)" as s_kit
  component "host-side egress proxy\ndeny-by-default allowlist · DNS-gated\nraw TCP/UDP/ICMP + private IPs blocked" as s_egress
  component "host-side credential injection\nvalues never enter the VM · sbx secret set" as s_cred
  component "per-sandbox Docker Engine\nno host socket · no privilege" as s_engine
  component "microVM\nown kernel + rootfs · non-root + sudo\nsbx rm ⇒ ephemeral (VM + images + volumes)" as s_vm
}

p_egress ..> s_egress : collapses to a declarative allowlist
p_mitm   ..> s_egress : no MITM CA to mint / mount / trust
p_broker ..> s_cred   : same principle — inject, never expose
p_dlp    ..> s_kit    : deny-by-default ⇒ no non-allowlisted sink
p_dind   ..> s_engine : kills the privileged sidecar
p_harden ..> s_vm     : hypervisor is the boundary
p_uid    ..> s_vm     : sandbox-managed user
p_life   ..> s_vm     : sbx rm deletes the VM

note right of sbx #E7F0FF
  **Advantages / simplifications**
  • one ""sbx run"" replaces the ""doRun""/""execWithEgress"" orchestration
  • a declarative allowlist replaces the ""plan.go"" multi-net + MITM topology
  • host-side credential injection already matches proveo's broker (convergent design)
  • a private Docker Engine per sandbox removes privileged DinD + its consent gating
  • deletes ~5 sidecar images and the per-session CA mint/mount/trust machinery
  • the hypervisor boundary makes the in-guest hardening no longer load-bearing
end note

note bottom of today #FFF6E5
  **Caveats — why this stays an experiment**
  • platform-gated: macOS Apple-Silicon · Linux + KVM · Win11 Hyper-V
    (proveo runs anywhere Docker does)
  • ""sbx"" v0.35 — "generally stable" but no formal GA yet
  • microVM RAM overhead (default 50% of host, cap 32 GiB); enforced network/fs
    policy + audit logs are a **paid** org tier
  • DLP **content** scan (base64/entropy on payloads to *allowed* hosts) has **no
    sandbox equivalent** — the proxy allowlists domains + injects headers, it is
    NOT a TLS-terminating body inspector → a capability gap, not just a simplification
  • ""sbx"" ships its own agent templates ⇒ adoption reframes proveo as
    **Kits/templates on sbx** (re-expressing the harness images, the run capability
    picker, the LSP/browser layers), not a ""docker run"" wrapper
end note

@enduml
